  "Increases": "",
  "Stays the same": "",
  "Becomes zero": "",
  "Decreases": "",
  "Going down a group, atoms get larger and outer electrons are farther from the nucleus with more shielding. This makes it easier to lose valence electrons, so metals become more reactive (e.g., Cs > Na > Li).": "",
