  "The octet rule states that atoms tend to:": "",
  "Exist in groups of 8": "",
  "Gain, lose, or share electrons to have 8 valence electrons": "",
  "Form exactly 8 bonds": "",
  "Always have 8 total electrons": "",
  "The octet rule drives most chemical bonding. Atoms achieve stability by having 8 electrons in their valence shell (like noble gases). Exceptions include hydrogen (duet rule: 2 electrons) and some expanded octets.": "",
  "How many valence electrons does carbon (Group 14) have?": "",
  "6": "",
